http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Canoe-sprint-championship-in-Kollam/article14004528.ece

The 26th National Canoe Sprint Championship for juniors and sub-juniors will be held on the Ashtamudi lake here from January 19 to 23.The event will be formally inaugurated by the Sports Minister Thiruvanchoor Radhakrishnan on January 20.It is the first time that the national sprint championship was being held at Kollam. Chief Mnister Oommen Chandy will inaugurate the valedictory function.General convener for the event D. Rajkumar Unni told media persons that Kollam was selected to host the event after identifying the Asramam creek of the Ashtamudi Lake as an ideal location for conducting the event.Competitions will be held from 7 a.m. to 6 p.m.More than 500 competitors from almost 20 States or Union Territories will participate in the event.